The Nelspruit Lions Club made and donated over 50 litres of soup to the Nelspruit Community Forum on Damascus Farm in Claremont on Sunday afternoon, July 17. The club had nominated Nelspruit Community Forum after registering with the organisation Chefs with Compassion, which had pledged to distribute 67 000 litres of soup to people and families who need it most. ALSO READ: A venture into the hidden Spekboom Valley with Mpumalanga Heritage experiencing The Nelspruit Lions Club had set a goal of 25 litres of soup, but managed to donate over 50 litres. Do you have more information about the story? Please send us an email to editorial@lowvelder.co.za. For free breaking and community news, visit Lowvelder’s website: Lowvelder For more news and interesting articles, like Lowvelder on Facebook, follow us on Twitter or Instagram